{{BLP primary sources|date=June 2008}}

'''Jeffrey H. Goodman''' is a neuroscientist at [[Helen Hayes Hospital]] in [[West Haverstraw, New York]]. His work studying treatments for [[Epilepsy]] has been published in many journals (H-index 30)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=GeApOFkAAAAJ&hl=en|title=Jeffrey H. Goodman - Google Scholar Citations|website=scholar.google.com|access-date=2018-09-07}}</ref> and presented at conferences all over the world{{Citation needed|date=May 2008}}. One of his recent publications involves a procedure for delivering a low frequency sine wave stimulation as a possible treatment {{Citation needed|date=May 2008}}. This abstract, co-authored by [[Jane Schon]], [[Sudarshan Phani]], and [[Jared Zucker]], was published in the 2006 Abstract publication of Epilepsia (published by the [[American Epilepsy Society]]).

Goodman has two daughters.

