'''Wilhelm Eichenberg''' (fl. 1930s) was a geologist and zoologist known for having described the class [[conodont|Conodonta]] of prehistoric jawless fish in 1930.<ref>Conodonten aus dem Culm des Harzes. W Eichenberg, Paläontologische Zeitschrift, 1930, page 177-182, {{doi|10.1007/BF03044446}}</ref>

